	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Dwedit wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Some boards support custom mirroring, and can create mirroring configurations that don't match one of the standard types.<br />[...]<br />Also, some boards can map ROM into the nametables.</div><br />Worst case scenario, you read all four memory locations and compare against a string instead.<br /><br />Edit: I assumed this was for hardwired mirroring. I don't know of any boards that have nametable ROM hardwired, or have a nonstandard mirroring configuration hardwired; it's only mappers that do that. That and there's no reason to be trying to detect the mirroring configuration of a cart that uses mapper-controlled mirroring, because it's completely dependent on the software. Thus, I think my method is appropriate for detecting the mirroring of a cart that has it hardwired.

		

